{
    "word": "Wiseacre",
    "definitions": [
        "A learned or wise man.",
        "One who makes undue pretensions to wisdom; a would-be-wise person; hence, in contempt, a simpleton; a dunce."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "Pythagoras learned much . . . becoming a mighty wiseacre."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OD. wijssegger or G. weissager a foreteller, prophet, from weissagen to foretell, to prophesy, OHG. w, corrupted (as if compounded of the words for wise and say) fr. w, fr. w a prophet, akin to AS. w, w, from the root of E. wit. See Wit, v.]"
}